As with my experience with the Ring and Signs is this: I wish that other people would shut the hell up when watching scarry movies. Ok, I know folks will scream and freak out when something scarry happens, but please for the love of God (or whoever else you worship or don't)... when something scarry is going to happen, don't go &quot;Booo&quot; to your girlfriend/wife/boyfriend/significant other to try and get them to freak out before the scary part actually happens! Crimeny!<br>
There was a scarry part that happened that I couldn't help but laugh at because someone in the audience just FREAKED. Remember the part when Rachelle was watching the tape in the farmers house, and then you see the farmer standing behind her when the light from the light house shines on them? This lady a couple seats down just SCREAMS like someone was killing her! I have never heard anyone scream like that before in a movie.<br>
<br>
Spoilers!!!!<br>
<br>
There were a couple parts that freaked me out. What really got me freaked was when the kid was coming out of the well and when she was walking she was moving unnaturally and they would skip frames. Freaky! Also, when she comes out of the TV... then kind of warps forward a few feet towards the guy... that was really cool! It was freaky in a cool way!<br>
<br>
My next part here is to ask what people thought of the ending to The Ring? Did anyone get what the Ring really is?<br>
Why did Rachelle live while the other guy died? Why did her son freak out when he found out they found the girls body? Why then does Rachelle make another copy of the tape and tells her son to make someone else watch it?<br>
My wife and I were talking about it and came to this conclusion. A ring or circle has no beginnng and no end. That's what the &quot;Ring&quot; is. The tape is supposed to be seen and passed onto others. If someone sees it and doesn't show it to someone else, they will die. If that person shows it to someone else, they live. Then the other person has to pass it on to survive. Think of those chain letters you used to get that said something bad would happen if you didn't pass it on.<br>
The four teens died because they didn't show it to anyone else. The guy (Rachelles' friend) eventually dies because he doesn't show the tape to anyone else. Rachelle lives because she shows the tape to her friend. Remember at the end when her son says: &quot;She wants to be heard&quot; (or something along those lines)? That's why she makes another copy of the tape for her son and tells him to show it too someone.<br>
Break the ring, you die.<br>
 <p>Komikino/Richman&lt;br&gt;<br>
